# Objective
  This project is for Create, Modify, Delete, Update the history of items.
  The applicaton is in python and working on AWS lambda and API gateway and dynamodb.
  AWS structure is handled by serverless.yml.
  Two staged is needed, dev and op and there is a way to select the stage before test and deploy.

# environment setup
  Python3.10 is needed.
  serverless framework is needed.
  AWS CLI is needed and configured with the proper user which has the permission to handle the resources.
  resources/env.json to set the environment variables for each stage.
  The npm script should be supported to deploy or remove AWS resources.
  pythonRequirement is with the option "slim: true"

# Pages.
## Login.
  Google OAuth2 is used for login.
  There is a dynamodb for the allowed user's email.
  There a admin email. This email should be set in the env.json file and it should be added to the allowed user's email in lambda.
### For the admin email
  allow to login even if it is not in the allowed user's email table.
### For others
  First login attempt, show the message "You are not allowed to access this application. Please wait for the admin to add your email to the allowed user's email list."
## User management page.
  Only admin can access this page.
  Show the all user email list to allow, remove, or forbidden the email.
## Data Page
  Default is only show 2 weeks data.
  Next or Prev button show the next or prev data.
  Add data at the top of the table.
  Radion button to remove or edit the item.
  Confirm remove popup and Edit page should be supported.
## Searching page.
  Searching options
  1. date range.
  2. name.
  3. text for searching all element.
